                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14105860" author="thobbs" created="Thu, 21 Aug 2014 19:57:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;7815.txt uses a timeout on the Condition await so that the main thread wakes up periodically.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14105942" author="mishail" created="Thu, 21 Aug 2014 20:53:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I believe we should add &lt;tt&gt;self._task_counter.await()&lt;/tt&gt; after &lt;tt&gt;sys.stdout.write(&apos;Aborting due to keyboard interrupt\n&apos;)&lt;/tt&gt;. Setting the signal doesn&apos;t mean all the task are completed immediately, so we have to wait until all of them are done, and only then return&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14105958" author="thobbs" created="Thu, 21 Aug 2014 21:00:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Good point.  The v2 patch does that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14105959" author="mishail" created="Thu, 21 Aug 2014 21:02:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14105965" author="thobbs" created="Thu, 21 Aug 2014 21:09:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks! Committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
